649
00:33:08,200 --> 00:33:09,467
I've already forgiven you.

650
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:12,033
You had the right to choose your happiness.

651
00:33:12,567 --> 00:33:13,467
I'm fine now.

652
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:16,900
So

653
00:33:18,100 --> 00:33:18,967
does that mean

654
00:33:18,967 --> 00:33:20,467
you'll come home for New Year's Eve?

655
00:33:23,033 --> 00:33:23,767
I'll think about it.

656
00:33:24,833 --> 00:33:26,367
Please go back. It's so cold out.

657
00:33:27,100 --> 00:33:27,667
Oh...

658
00:33:27,767 --> 00:33:28,667
Hey...

659
00:33:29,100 --> 00:33:29,867
When the time comes

660
00:33:31,067 --> 00:33:32,967
tell me what you want to eat

661
00:33:32,967 --> 00:33:33,633
Jiang.

662
00:33:33,733 --> 00:33:35,967
Let me know when you're off for Spring Festival break!

663
00:33:48,567 --> 00:33:49,167
Who is he?

664
00:33:49,533 --> 00:33:50,767
Sang Yan. Can't you recognize him?

665
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:53,033
He's been sleeping for several days.

666
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:54,267
If he keeps this up

667
00:33:54,267 --> 00:33:55,400
he'll probably spend the Spring Festival here.

668
00:34:16,100 --> 00:34:16,800
Dian

669
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:17,533
I need to ask you.

670
00:34:17,633 --> 00:34:19,833
Did you have an argument with Sang Yan?

671
00:34:20,300 --> 00:34:21,000
No.

672
00:34:21,767 --> 00:34:23,333
Then why has he been sleeping at the Overtime

673
00:34:23,333 --> 00:34:23,933
not going back home?

674
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:25,200
He's been sleeping at the Overtime?

675
00:34:25,267 --> 00:34:25,867
Yes.

676
00:34:26,833 --> 00:34:28,167
If Sang Yan bullies you

677
00:34:28,167 --> 00:34:28,833
you must let me know.

678
00:34:28,833 --> 00:34:30,233
I won't let him off the hook.

679
00:34:30,367 --> 00:34:31,400
You're overthinking.

680
00:34:32,200 --> 00:34:32,767
Come here.

681
00:34:32,767 --> 00:34:33,633
It's not that I think too much.

682
00:34:33,633 --> 00:34:34,233
What's wrong?

683
00:34:34,233 --> 00:34:35,833
It's just that you never tell me anything

684
00:34:35,833 --> 00:34:37,200
about how you two get along.

685
00:34:37,667 --> 00:34:39,600
We're not really getting along.

686
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:41,567
Actually, I think

687
00:34:42,167 --> 00:34:44,067
we're more like

688
00:34:45,567 --> 00:34:47,700
two strangers under one roof.

689
00:34:48,933 --> 00:34:50,967
And we don't really talk much.

690
00:34:51,700 --> 00:34:52,867
Dian, let's leave it at that.

691
00:34:52,867 --> 00:34:53,600
Bye then.

692
00:35:01,633 --> 00:35:04,167
[Lock the door]

693
00:35:05,533 --> 00:35:06,667
Not coming back again?

694
00:35:11,433 --> 00:35:15,233
[Okay]

695
00:35:27,967 --> 00:35:29,800
Thanks for helping with the Overtime photoshoot.

696
00:35:30,533 --> 00:35:31,300
No problem.

697
00:35:31,467 --> 00:35:32,267
You can go back now.

698
00:35:32,267 --> 00:35:33,067
No need to walk me out.

699
00:35:33,867 --> 00:35:35,467
Do you always

700
00:35:35,467 --> 00:35:36,667
walk every girl home?

701
00:35:37,833 --> 00:35:38,800
You're a girl.

702
00:35:38,800 --> 00:35:40,833
It's not safe to walk home alone at night.

703
00:35:42,600 --> 00:35:43,967
You're a guy.

704
00:35:43,967 --> 00:35:45,967
Be mindful of what you say.

705
00:35:46,033 --> 00:35:47,267
Don't act all macho.

706
00:35:52,067 --> 00:35:53,100
You don't need to walk me out.

707
00:35:53,300 --> 00:35:54,300
My house is just up ahead.

708
00:35:54,300 --> 00:35:55,067
Qiao

709
00:35:56,100 --> 00:35:57,000
where are you going?

710
00:35:57,600 --> 00:35:58,767
Why aren't you coming home?

711
00:35:59,967 --> 00:36:01,033
Is that your friend?

712
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:03,367
Yeah, friend!

713
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:05,967
Hello!

714
00:36:07,100 --> 00:36:08,633
Auntie, who's that?

715
00:36:09,033 --> 00:36:10,800
Is that your boyfriend?

716
00:36:11,567 --> 00:36:13,267
Stop making things up!

717
00:36:13,433 --> 00:36:15,200
So your house is around here?

718
00:36:16,567 --> 00:36:17,767
Come in for tea!

719
00:36:18,433 --> 00:36:19,800
Don't be shy. Come in!

720
00:36:20,567 --> 00:36:21,067
Okay!

721
00:36:21,300 --> 00:36:21,967
Stop looking.

722
00:36:23,033 --> 00:36:24,567
You don't really want tea, do you?

723
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:26,233
Of course, I don't.

724
00:36:26,433 --> 00:36:27,467
I just don't want them to overthink it.

725
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:28,933
That'll definitely make them think.

726
00:36:30,233 --> 00:36:31,100
Well, I'm off now.

727
00:36:31,633 --> 00:36:32,233
Goodnight.

728
00:36:32,867 --> 00:36:33,467
Goodnight.

729
00:36:44,100 --> 00:36:45,533
Stop staring.

730
00:36:45,667 --> 00:36:46,400
Naughty ones.

731
00:36:53,900 --> 00:36:55,833
[Dear Grandma]

732
00:36:57,367 --> 00:36:58,433
Hey, Grandma.

733
00:36:58,833 --> 00:37:00,100
Are you going home yet?

734
00:37:00,233 --> 00:37:01,600
I miss you so much.

735
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:02,600
Haoan

736
00:37:02,833 --> 00:37:04,400
Do you have

737
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:05,800
a girlfriend

738
00:37:05,800 --> 00:37:06,867
named...

739
00:37:07,700 --> 00:37:08,767
Her name is Wang Linlin.

740
00:37:09,200 --> 00:37:09,933
Really?

741
00:37:09,933 --> 00:37:10,967
In a few days

742
00:37:10,967 --> 00:37:11,933
I want to meet her.

743
00:37:11,933 --> 00:37:12,467
Ah?

744
00:37:20,933 --> 00:37:24,033
[Happy New Year]

745
00:37:24,033 --> 00:37:24,700
Alright.

746
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:26,367
Okay.

747
00:37:27,767 --> 00:37:28,533
Don't worry.

748
00:37:28,533 --> 00:37:30,033
I'll definitely alter your voice for the media.

749
00:37:30,933 --> 00:37:31,567
Yes.

750
00:37:32,067 --> 00:37:33,833
Your privacy will be completely protected.

751
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:35,567
Okay, thanks.

752
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:40,933
Yifan.

753
00:37:41,633 --> 00:37:42,233
Yifan.

754
00:37:44,967 --> 00:37:45,933
Let me show you something fun.

755
00:37:47,633 --> 00:37:48,200
Look.

756
00:37:49,233 --> 00:37:50,633
That interview with your classmate

757
00:37:50,633 --> 00:37:52,167
[First place]
was featured in the news.

758
00:37:52,600 --> 00:37:53,567
[Handsome, does your face have insurance?]
A netizen

759
00:37:53,767 --> 00:37:56,033
[This guy is both handsome and miserable]
compiled a popular news collection.

760
00:37:56,233 --> 00:37:57,400
He included this clip too.

761
00:37:57,533 --> 00:37:58,933
Who knew that it became so popular.

762
00:37:59,300 --> 00:38:00,267
This classmate of yours

763
00:38:00,267 --> 00:38:02,600
made it to the top ten most popular figures online.

764
00:38:02,600 --> 00:38:03,767
He even trended on social media.

765
00:38:05,300 --> 00:38:06,533
[Happy]
With this clip of him

766
00:38:06,633 --> 00:38:08,933
[This handsome guy is so miserable, lost his house]
our year-end review should be fine.

767
00:38:09,033 --> 00:38:10,533
It really matches what I said

768
00:38:10,533 --> 00:38:11,867
that he was both amazing and miserable.

769
00:38:12,033 --> 00:38:14,200
Now everyone calls him "Handsome and Miserable."

770
00:38:15,933 --> 00:38:18,967
You didn't even blur his face out?

771
00:38:18,967 --> 00:38:20,267
Won't it affect him?

772
00:38:21,233 --> 00:38:21,833
No.

773
00:38:21,833 --> 00:38:23,233
He signed a consent form.

774
00:38:23,267 --> 00:38:24,267
Look at the comments

775
00:38:24,267 --> 00:38:25,567
everyone is praising how handsome he is.

776
00:38:26,700 --> 00:38:27,833
I'll go tell Ms. Liu.

777
00:38:28,300 --> 00:38:29,633
Ms. Liu!

778
00:38:41,833 --> 00:38:43,333
[Jiang, how about I make these dishes for you during the holiday?]

779
00:38:43,333 --> 00:38:45,833
[Preparing for a family reunion]

780
00:38:46,033 --> 00:38:48,033
[Safe and Happy]

781
00:39:03,667 --> 00:39:05,300
Is there anything you want to say now?

782
00:39:07,100 --> 00:39:09,000
Happy... I'm really happy.

783
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:09,533
Happy...

784
00:39:09,533 --> 00:39:11,300
I hope you can be as happy as I am.

785
00:39:11,300 --> 00:39:13,767
Happy...

786
00:39:14,400 --> 00:39:15,467
It's really interesting.

787
00:39:16,667 --> 00:39:18,200
My sister and mom both like watching it.

788
00:39:18,633 --> 00:39:19,433
They even sent this clip

789
00:39:19,433 --> 00:39:20,700
to our big family group.

790
00:39:22,233 --> 00:39:23,633
You scared me to death.

791
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:26,800
Why are you back?

792
00:39:27,233 --> 00:39:29,200
I rented the apartment myself.

793
00:39:29,300 --> 00:39:30,567
Wouldn't it be a waste not to stay here?

794
00:39:30,833 --> 00:39:31,467
True.

795
00:39:34,633 --> 00:39:36,300
But why didn't you turn on a light at home?

796
00:39:46,233 --> 00:39:47,267
You're not going back for the holiday?

797
00:39:48,067 --> 00:39:48,967
It depends on my mood.

798
00:39:53,767 --> 00:39:55,033
Why are there so many things here?

799
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:57,167
Aren't those two shelves all mine?

800
00:40:04,300 --> 00:40:05,367
Drinking coffee in the middle of the night?

801
00:40:05,367 --> 00:40:06,433
You might not be able to sleep.

802
00:40:11,600 --> 00:40:12,600
Where's my coffee?

803
00:40:14,233 --> 00:40:14,967
I drank it.

804
00:40:15,867 --> 00:40:16,933
It had already expired

805
00:40:16,933 --> 00:40:17,600
so I threw it away.

806
00:40:17,600 --> 00:40:18,467
You can drink mine.

807
00:40:26,367 --> 00:40:27,433
How much is it?

808
00:40:27,433 --> 00:40:28,267
I'll transfer it to you.

809
00:40:29,033 --> 00:40:29,667
No need.

810
00:40:30,867 --> 00:40:31,800
If I'm not here

811
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:33,267
help me deal with the stuff in the fridge.

812
00:40:34,033 --> 00:40:34,967
It can't be stored long anyway.

813
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:35,967
I don't like wasting things.

814
00:40:36,967 --> 00:40:38,467
Let's just say we bought it together.

815
00:40:38,467 --> 00:40:39,967
How much was it?

816
00:40:40,467 --> 00:40:42,067
Just treat it as me asking you for a favor.

817
00:40:46,533 --> 00:40:48,200
Didn't we agree

818
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:49,467
that we'll split all the costs?

819
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:01,433
A favor?

820
00:41:02,967 --> 00:41:03,933
What kind of favor?

821
00:41:10,533 --> 00:41:11,767
Cleaning up the kitchen scraps?

822
00:41:22,433 --> 00:41:24,100
[Let's calculate it. How much do I owe you?]

823
00:41:39,600 --> 00:41:40,467
Twenty?

824
00:41:51,667 --> 00:41:54,633
[You owe me.]

825
00:41:55,667 --> 00:41:56,800
When?

826
00:42:04,667 --> 00:42:05,433
Dian

827
00:42:05,833 --> 00:42:07,533
how do you plan to spend the Spring Festival?

828
00:42:08,167 --> 00:42:08,933
I haven't decided yet.

829
00:42:09,567 --> 00:42:11,400
How about you come to my place for the holiday?

830
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:12,433
Let's celebrate together.

831
00:42:12,633 --> 00:42:13,267
Sure.

832
00:42:13,700 --> 00:42:15,367
But I don't feel like running that far.

833
00:42:16,533 --> 00:42:17,933
If you're spending the holiday alone

834
00:42:17,933 --> 00:42:19,067
won't it be boring?

835
00:42:19,433 --> 00:42:21,533
I plan to sleep for three days and nights.

836
00:42:21,667 --> 00:42:22,867
Make up for all the lost sleep

837
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:24,933
from all the overtime.

838
00:42:26,100 --> 00:42:27,033
What about Sang Yan?

839
00:42:27,033 --> 00:42:28,100
Is he going home for the holiday?

840
00:42:28,267 --> 00:42:29,433
He'll definitely go home.

841
00:42:29,633 --> 00:42:30,800
His family's local.

842
00:42:31,100 --> 00:42:31,867
And he's not

843
00:42:31,867 --> 00:42:33,067
on bad terms with his family.

844
00:42:33,767 --> 00:42:35,300
Why suddenly bring up Sang Yan?

845
00:42:35,933 --> 00:42:37,600
It's just that you never tell me anything

846
00:42:37,600 --> 00:42:38,933
about how you two get along.

847
00:42:40,833 --> 00:42:43,067
We're not really getting along.

848
00:42:43,633 --> 00:42:44,867
Actually, I think

849
00:42:45,533 --> 00:42:47,433
we're more like

850
00:42:48,267 --> 00:42:50,467
two strangers under one roof.

851
00:42:52,967 --> 00:42:55,167
And we don't really talk much.

852
00:42:56,767 --> 00:43:03,533
[Episode 5]
[Get Closer, Would You?]

853
00:43:10,633 --> 00:43:11,433
Six threes.

854
00:43:11,433 --> 00:43:12,800
[The story is not over yet...]

855
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:13,600
Ten fours.

856
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:15,200
Ten fives.

857
00:43:21,433 --> 00:43:24,800
Fifteen...

858
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:25,633
Twenty sixs.

859
00:43:27,467 --> 00:43:28,867
What exactly are you shouting?

860
00:43:33,933 --> 00:43:34,800
I've already self-destructed.

861
00:43:34,800 --> 00:43:35,833
Just yell "open" and you win.

862
00:43:38,100 --> 00:43:39,700
What's that look in your eyes?

863
00:43:39,800 --> 00:43:41,233
Are you calling downward or opening?

864
00:43:41,400 --> 00:43:43,600
Can't you see I've been helping you?

865
00:43:43,600 --> 00:43:44,300
Open.

866
00:43:45,567 --> 00:43:46,767
Totally can't tell.

867
00:43:47,200 --> 00:43:48,467
Can't you just say it directly?

868
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:49,833
Without me

869
00:43:49,833 --> 00:43:51,000
you'd lose every round.

870
00:43:51,667 --> 00:43:52,167
Open.

871
00:43:52,867 --> 00:43:54,267
So does that mean...

872
00:43:59,067 --> 00:43:59,600
Open.

873
00:44:00,400 --> 00:44:01,600
You finally understood what I meant.

874
00:44:03,200 --> 00:44:03,800
I lost.

875
00:44:05,400 --> 00:44:07,867
Sang Yan, you finally lost.

876
00:44:07,867 --> 00:44:08,967
No regrets in my life.

877
00:44:08,967 --> 00:44:11,033
Come on, Truth and Dare.

878
00:44:17,500 --> 00:44:18,833
♪Even the strongest heart♪

879
00:44:19,067 --> 00:44:20,733
♪Can waver♪

880
00:44:21,100 --> 00:44:24,300
♪And doubt its fire♪

881
00:44:24,533 --> 00:44:26,167
♪But you never lost faith in me♪

882
00:44:26,167 --> 00:44:27,867
♪In every battle, every dream I chased♪

883
00:44:28,067 --> 00:44:30,733
♪There is meaning in every step I made♪

884
00:44:31,567 --> 00:44:37,533
♪Through the storm, through the endless night♪

885
00:44:37,900 --> 00:44:39,533
♪You were there, shining like a light♪

886
00:44:39,533 --> 00:44:41,233
♪Warm and bright♪

887
00:44:41,367 --> 00:44:45,100
♪Standing right by my side♪

888
00:44:45,533 --> 00:44:51,667
♪It was you, striding toward me through the storm♪

889
00:44:52,033 --> 00:44:58,933
♪It was you, always cheering me on♪

890
00:44:59,100 --> 00:45:02,100
♪The road is rough♪

891
00:45:02,433 --> 00:45:06,533
♪The rain won't stop♪

892
00:45:06,733 --> 00:45:10,700
♪But with you here♪

893
00:45:10,967 --> 00:45:17,033
♪I fear no dark♪

894
00:45:20,267 --> 00:45:23,867
♪Every thought, every memory is filled with you♪

895
00:45:24,167 --> 00:45:27,667
♪Marking our youth with every step we took♪

896
00:45:27,933 --> 00:45:29,833
♪When the downpour falls from the sky♪

897
00:45:29,833 --> 00:45:33,467
♪You're the one holding out an umbrella for me♪

898
00:45:33,833 --> 00:45:37,367
♪When the white dove brings the news♪

899
00:45:37,733 --> 00:45:41,167
♪You're the first I want to tell♪

900
00:45:41,567 --> 00:45:50,233
♪I won't give up. I'll stay right here with you♪

901
00:45:54,833 --> 00:46:01,033
♪It was you, striding toward me through the storm♪

902
00:46:01,867 --> 00:46:08,300
♪It was you, always cheering me on♪

903
00:46:08,300 --> 00:46:11,467
♪The road is rough♪

904
00:46:11,933 --> 00:46:15,900
♪The rain won't stop♪

905
00:46:16,100 --> 00:46:18,733
♪But with you here♪

906
00:46:18,933 --> 00:46:22,767
♪I will never give up♪

907
00:46:23,067 --> 00:46:29,133
♪You are my courage, my hope for the sky beyond♪

908
00:46:29,667 --> 00:46:35,500
♪You are my light, shining through every night♪

909
00:46:36,067 --> 00:46:38,900
♪Even if I have to walk alone someday♪

910
00:46:39,333 --> 00:46:42,167
♪I'll never truly be on my own♪

911
00:46:43,233 --> 00:46:47,733
♪'Cause knowing you're here♪

912
00:46:48,167 --> 00:46:54,767
♪I can brave the dark ahead♪

913
00:46:56,567 --> 00:46:57,833
[Huge thanks to everyone involved and to all the fans of The First Frost!]
